<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880223-0022 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: American Standard Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AST </CO><TEXT>   American Standard Inc., the target of a $2.03 billion hostile tender offer by Black andamp; Decker Inc., said it obtained commitments from four banks to fund a previously announced $1.84 billion recapitalization plan.    The commitments, subject to definitive documentation, are with Chemical Bank; Citibank; Manufacturers Hanover Trust Co.; and Sumitomo Bank Ltd.    American Standard is a maker of air-conditioning, building and transportation products. Black andamp; Decker is a Towson, Md.-based maker of power tools and household appliances.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, American Standard shares closed at $68.125, up 50 cents. </TEXT></DOC>